  "texts": [
    "E.1 Main EntryWe follow the RL process, as shown in the code below, where we initialize the dataset and construct environment for subsequent training and inference.1 # load config 2 cfg = Config.fromfile(config_path) 3 # build dataset 4 dataset = DATASET.build(cfg.dataset) 5 # build environment 6 env = ENVIRONMENT.build(cfg.environment) 7 # init environment 8 state, info = env.reset() 9 # execute steps 10 while True: 11 action = run_step(cfg, state, info,...) 12 state, reward, done, truncated, info = env.step(action) 13 if done: 14 break 15 # done E.2 Run StepThe whole process is mainly through the global params storage and transimit parameters, we do not list the parameter transmition process in detail here.",
    "To execute each step, the following primary procedures are adhered to:1 # global params 2 params = dict() 3 # plot Kline chart 4 kline_path = plots.plot_kline(state, info,...) 5 params.update({\"kline_path\": kline_path}) 6 # prepare tools params 7 tools_params = prepared_tools_params(state, info,...) 8 params.update(tools_params) 9 # 01 -latest market intelligence 10 template = read_resource_file(...) # load latest market intelligence prompt template 11 lmi = PROMPT.build(...) # build instance 12 lmi_res = lmi.run(state, info, params, template,...) # run 13 # 02 -retrieve the past market intelligence retrieved_params = retrieve_pmi(state, info, params, memory, diverse_query,...) params.update(retrieved_params) # 03 -add latest market intelligence to memory lmi.add_to_memory(lmi_res, memory,...) # 04 -past market intelligence template = read_resource_file(...) # load past market intelligence prompt template pmi = PROMPT.build(...) # build instance pmi_res = pmi.run(state, info, params, template,...) # run # 05 -low-level reflection template = read_resource_file(...) # load low level reflection prompt template llr = PROMPT.build(...) # build instance llr_res = llr.run(state, info, params, template,...) # run # 06 -retrieve the past low-level reflection retrieved_params = retrieve_pllr(state, info, params, memory, diverse_query,...) params.update(retrieved_params) # 07 -add low-level reflection to memory llr.add_to_memory(llr_res, memory,...) # plot trading chart trading_path = plots.plot_trading(state, info,...) params.update({\"trading_path\": trading_path}) # 08 -high-level reflection template = read_resource_file(...) # load high level reflection prompt template hlr = PROMPT.build(...) # build instance hlr_res = hlr.run(state, info, params, template,...) # run # 09 -retrieve the past high-level reflection retrieved_params = retrieve_phlr(state, info, params, memory, diverse_query,...) params.update(retrieved_params) # 10 -add high-level reflection to memory hlr.add_to_memory(hlr_res, memory,...) # 11 -decision-making template = read_resource_file(...) # load decision-making prompt template decision = PROMPT.build(...) # build instance decision_res = decision.run(state, info, params, template,...) # run action, reasoning = decision_res[\"action\"], decision_res[\"reasoing\"] F DETAILS OF PROMPT DESIGNOur prompt templates are designed modularly, featuring separate templates for the latest and past market intelligence, low-level reflection, high-level reflection, and decision-making modules.",
    "These templates include variables marked as \"$$key$$\" within the \"params\" dictionary.",
    "Our template utilizes HTML for its ability to combine formatting with user-friendly visualizations.",
    "In our testing, we find that JSON's strict formatting requirements frequently lead to errors."
